Assignment 2: Software Requirements

Team: Project Group 6

Project Title: FitTracker

Members: Cole Johnson, Brian Mayorga, Fawaze Ouro-Koura, Isaac Sarmiento-Herrera, Tony Thompson


Stakeholders | Requirements
Users | FR1 - FR15, FR17 - FR 19
Servers | FR20
All | FR16


Functional

FR1. User Progress Tracking
Goal: Users can track their daily progress.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: The app will log and display users daily exercise, sleep, and diet intake.
Origin: 1st meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 1




FR2. 30-Day Progress Graph
Goal: Users can view their progress over the past month.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: This app will provide a graphical representation of their progress from the last 30 days.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 2




FR3. Input Exercise Data
Goal: Users can input their exercise activities.
Stakeholders: Users
Description:  The user will be allowed to enter their workouts, including type, duration, and sets.
Origin: 1st  meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 3




FR4. Input Calorie Data
Goal: Users can track their daily calorie/protein intake.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: This app will allow the user to input foods that they consumed to calculate calories.
Origin: 1st  meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 3




FR5. Sleep Tracking
Goal: Users can log and monitor their sleep patterns.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: The app will allow users to input sleep times and durations to figure out the sleep quality.
Origin: 1st meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 2




FR6. Bottom Navigation Tabs
Goal: Users can easily access different parts of the app
Stakeholders: Users
Description: The app will have a tabbed navigation system for quick access at the bottom.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 3





FR7. Time of day greeting
Goal: User will be greeted by program depending on time of day
Stakeholders: User
Description: If the user opens the application in the morning, afternoon, or at night. The application will greet the user differently (ex. Mornings - “Good morning [user’s name], here’s your progress:”). Program will be able to detect the time of day.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 1




FR8. Accurate Wellness Suggestions
Goal: User will have accurate suggestions catered to them
Stakeholders: Users
Description: Program will be able to provide accurate wellness recommendations provided by the user’s data.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version:1.0
Date:10/1/2024
Priority: 4




FR9. Touch Gestures
Goal: Users can scroll by swiping their screen.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: Program can register user touch inputs to know to scroll up or down on a given screen.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 3




FR10. Timer
Goal: User can input the amount of seconds, minutes, hours, or initiate a stopwatch.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: Ask users to set or initiate a time cycle/duration for said exercise(s) or workout.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 2




FR11. Notifications for Missed Goals
Goal:Users will receive notifications if they miss daily goals (exercise, sleep, or diet).
Stakeholders: Users
Description:The app will send reminders to users when they fail to meet their set fitness goals for the day.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 2




FR12. Custom Goal Setting
Goal:Users can set custom fitness goals.
Stakeholders: Users
Description:The app will allow users to define and customize their daily fitness, nutrition, or sleep goals.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 3


FR13.Workout Routines Library
Goal:Users can access pre-made workout routines.
Stakeholders: Users
Description:The app will provide a library of workout routines categorized by fitness goals (e.g., strength training, cardio, flexibility) that users can follow and log.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 2


FR14.Personalized Dashboard
Goal:Users will have a personalized dashboard view.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: Each user will be able to view a customized dashboard displaying their key fitness stats, goals, and progress.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 4


FR15. Goal Achievement Badges
Goal:Users can earn badges for achieving fitness milestones.
Stakeholders: Users
Description:The app will reward users with virtual badges for completing specific fitness goals, such as reaching a target number of workouts or achieving a personal best.
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 5

Non Functional

FR16.Performance Requirements
Goal: Ensure the app runs smoothly without lag.
Stakeholders: All
Description: The app should load pages and process inputs within 1-2 seconds to provide a seamless user experience.
Origin: 2nd Meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 1



FR17. Usability Requirements
Goal: Make the app intuitive and easy to use.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: The app should be easy to navigate for users of all ages and technical expertise, with clear instructions and minimal learning curve
Origin: 2nd meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 2



FR18. Color Scheme
Goal: User can change the color theme of the FitnessTrack application.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: User can enable different display colors, e.g., dark/light/normal/(color-blind mode).
Origin: September 27th, 2024


Version: 1.0
Date: 10/1/2024
Priority: 1



FR19. Compatibility Requirements
Goal: Ensure cross-platform functionality.
Stakeholders: Users
Description: The application should work on IOS and Android devices.
Origin: 1st meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 9/30/2024
Priority:1



FR20. Security Requirements
Goal: Keep the user data protected.
Stakeholders: Server
Description: Data must be stored securely and comply with privacy regulations.
Origin: 1st meeting


Version: 1.0
Date: 9/30/2024
Priority: 1


